<div class="container">
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;"><a href="/blog/" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.7);font-size:0.9rem;text-decoration:none;">← Back to Blog</a></p>
<h1>Same-Day Insurance Replacement Rentals in Black River Falls — Exactly What to Do After an Accident</h1>
<p>You just had a fender-bender. Your car needs to go to the shop. You have to be at work tomorrow. Here's the play-by-play.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="section">
<div class="container">
<div style="max-width:800px;margin:0 auto;">

<p>Most accidents happen on a Tuesday morning when you're already running late. By the time you've exchanged information with the other driver, called your insurance company, and arranged a tow to the body shop, the day is half gone — and you still don't have a way to pick up your kids from school, get to work tomorrow, or run the errands you were already behind on.</p>

<p>Here's the good news: an insurance replacement rental can be in your hands the same afternoon. Most local drivers don't realize how fast this can move when you know who to call and what to bring. This post walks you through exactly that.</p>

<h2>Step 1: Call your insurance adjuster before you do anything else</h2>
<p>Before you even think about a rental, get your claim opened. Call the claims line on your insurance card. Have these ready:</p>
<ul style="margin-bottom:24px;padding-left:20px;">
<li style="margin-bottom:8px;">Your policy number</li>
<li style="margin-bottom:8px;">The other driver's information (if it was a multi-car accident)</li>
<li style="margin-bottom:8px;">A description of the damage and where it happened</li>
<li style="margin-bottom:8px;">A police report number if one was filed</li>
</ul>
<p>The adjuster will give you a <strong>claim number</strong> on the spot. Write it down. You'll need this for everything that comes next, including the rental.</p>

<h2>Step 2: Confirm rental coverage on your policy</h2>
<p>While you've got the adjuster on the phone, ask one specific question: <em>"Does my policy include rental reimbursement, and what's the daily limit?"</em> Most full-coverage auto policies include a rental allowance — typically $30 to $50 per day, sometimes higher — for as long as your vehicle is in the shop. Some policies have a 30-day cap.</p>
<p>If your policy doesn't include rental coverage, you can still rent — you'll just pay out of pocket. But knowing the limit upfront lets you pick the right vehicle. A $35/day allowance covers our intermediate car comfortably; a higher allowance might let you upgrade to a full-size or minivan.</p>

<h2>Step 3: Call us with the claim number ready</h2>
<p>Once you have your claim number and rental coverage details, call us at <a href="tel:+17153961466"><strong>715-396-1466</strong></a>. Tell us:</p>
<ul style="margin-bottom:24px;padding-left:20px;">
<li style="margin-bottom:8px;">You need an insurance replacement rental</li>
<li style="margin-bottom:8px;">The name of your insurance company</li>
<li style="margin-bottom:8px;">Your claim number</li>
<li style="margin-bottom:8px;">Your adjuster's name and direct phone number</li>
<li style="margin-bottom:8px;">When you need the vehicle (often "today" works)</li>
</ul>
<p>We'll confirm the vehicle, call your adjuster to verify direct billing, and have the car ready when you arrive. In most cases this entire process takes under an hour.</p>

<h2>Step 4: Pick up the vehicle</h2>
<p>Bring these four things:</p>
<div style="background:#f8f9fb;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:8px;padding:24px;margin-bottom:32px;">
<ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0;">
<li style="padding:10px 0;border-bottom:1px solid #e5e7eb;"><strong>1. Your driver's license.</strong> Valid, current, and physically present. No exceptions.</li>
<li style="padding:10px 0;border-bottom:1px solid #e5e7eb;"><strong>2. Your insurance claim number.</strong> Written down or in a text — don't try to remember it.</li>
<li style="padding:10px 0;border-bottom:1px solid #e5e7eb;"><strong>3. Adjuster contact info.</strong> Name and phone number, in case we need to verify anything.</li>
<li style="padding:10px 0;"><strong>4. A credit or debit card.</strong> For the security deposit only — $300 for local renters, $500 for out-of-town. Insurance covers the rental cost; the deposit is yours back when you return the car.</li>
</ul>
</div>

<h2>Step 5: Drive away — and let us coordinate with the body shop</h2>
<p>This is where renting from a local independent matters. We work directly with body shops and dealerships throughout western Wisconsin — Black River Falls, Tomah, Sparta, Eau Claire, Neillsville. When your vehicle is repaired, the shop calls us. We coordinate the swap. You don't have to manage the logistics.</p>
<p>Most national chains route insurance replacement claims through a regional call center. We do it from our office, with a real person who knows the body shops by name.</p>

<h2>What renters say about emergency rentals</h2>
<div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;margin-bottom:16px;">
<span style="color:#f59e0b;font-size:1.1rem;letter-spacing:1px;" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars">★★★★★</span>
<span style="font-family:'Archivo',sans-serif;font-weight:600;color:var(--text-light);font-size:0.9rem;">5.0 on Google</span>
</div>
<div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-left:4px solid var(--navy);border-radius:8px;padding:24px;margin-bottom:20px;">
<p style="font-style:italic;color:var(--text);line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:16px;">"My car broke down late at night on my way to a business meeting in Eau Claire. I called Riverside Auto Rental and was able to reach Tas after hours. She immediately arranged a reliable rental for early the next morning. They truly go above and beyond — saved the day and made a stressful situation stress-free."</p>
<div style="font-family:'Archivo',sans-serif;font-weight:700;color:var(--navy);">Jim <span style="font-weight:400;color:var(--text-light);font-size:0.9rem;">— After-Hours Emergency Rental</span></div>
</div>
<div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-left:4px solid var(--navy);border-radius:8px;padding:24px;margin-bottom:20px;">
<p style="font-style:italic;color:var(--text);line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:16px;">"I rented a 15-passenger van for a family trip taking my daughters to a volleyball tournament in Kansas City. The entire rental process was completely seamless. Staff is super friendly, quick paperwork, and no hassle at all. The van was a perfect fit for our needs."</p>
<div style="font-family:'Archivo',sans-serif;font-weight:700;color:var(--navy);">Ben H. <span style="font-weight:400;color:var(--text-light);font-size:0.9rem;">— 15-Passenger Van Rental</span></div>
</div>
<p style="margin-bottom:32px;"><a href="https://search.google.com/local/reviews?placeid=ChIJe_gqTAjk_ocRVVpllXYH-zQ" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:var(--navy);font-weight:600;">Read all reviews on Google →</a></p>

<h2>One more thing: weekends and after-hours</h2>
<p>Accidents don't keep business hours. We don't always answer at 11 PM, but we do return calls early and we've made same-day Saturday-morning rentals happen for people who needed to be at a Sunday wedding or Monday meeting. If you need a vehicle outside our normal hours, leave a clear voicemail with your callback number — we'll get back to you faster than you'd expect.</p>

<h2>The bottom line</h2>
<p>An insurance replacement rental in Black River Falls isn't complicated, but it moves faster when you call a local rental that knows your insurance carrier, your body shop, and your area. Family-owned since 1983. We'll have a vehicle ready when you arrive — call <a href="tel:+17153961466"><strong>715-396-1466</strong></a> with your claim number in hand.</p>

<div style="margin-top:48px;">
<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<div class="faq-list">
<div class="faq-item">
<button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">Can I get a rental car the same day as my accident?
<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
</button>
<div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. Call early in the day with your claim number ready and we can usually have a vehicle for you within hours. Same-day Saturday rentals are possible too if you call before noon.</p></div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">Will my insurance company pay the rental directly?
<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
</button>
<div class="faq-answer"><p>In most cases, yes. We work directly with adjusters from major insurance companies and bill them for the rental. You're responsible only for the security deposit, which is refunded when you return the vehicle.</p></div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">What if my policy doesn't include rental coverage?
<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
</button>
<div class="faq-answer"><p>You can still rent — you'll just pay out of pocket. Daily rates start at $55 for an intermediate car. Weekly rates with unlimited mileage start at $450 and are usually a better deal if your repair will take more than 4 days.</p></div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">How long can I keep an insurance replacement rental?
<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
</button>
<div class="faq-answer"><p>As long as your insurance covers it. Most policies cap rental reimbursement at 30 days. We coordinate with your adjuster on extensions if your repair runs long.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

